# EduPortal GitHub proxy (optional)

Only needed if you don't want the GitHub token sitting in the browser for
the **Full Data Sync** feature (Owner Console → Full Data Sync). The
smaller "GitHub Registry Sync" (school registry + emails file) doesn't use
this — that one always uses the token typed directly into the browser.

## Deploy it

Requires a free [Cloudflare](https://dash.cloudflare.com/sign-up) account
and [wrangler](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/wrangler/install-and-update/)
(`npm install -g wrangler`).

```bash
cd proxy
wrangler login
wrangler secret put GITHUB_TOKEN   # paste your fine-grained PAT when prompted
wrangler secret put PROXY_KEY      # paste any random string when prompted
wrangler deploy
```

`wrangler deploy` prints the worker's URL, something like
`https://eduportal-github-proxy.<your-subdomain>.workers.dev`.

## Point EduPortal at it

In **Owner Console → Full Data Sync → "Route through a proxy instead of a
direct token"**:
- **Proxy URL**: the workers.dev URL from above
- **Proxy key**: the same random string you set as `PROXY_KEY`

Leave the main token/owner/repo fields as they are — owner/repo are still
sent (in the request path), just not the token.

## Token scope

Whatever PAT you put in `GITHUB_TOKEN`, make it a **fine-grained token
scoped to only this one repository's Contents (read and write)** — not a
classic token with broad access. The worker only ever forwards to
`https://api.github.com/repos/{owner}/{repo}/...`, so a narrowly-scoped
token can't do anything outside that repo even if the worker itself were
ever compromised.
